prompt:
A Linear issue status just changed. Post a summary to the project Slack channel.

## Context
Use the issue details from the automation trigger (id, title, url, status, description, assignee).

## Steps
1. Summarize what was completed in 1–2 sentences. Infer from the issue description, comments, linked PRs, and recent work if needed.
2. Check whether a GitHub PR exists for this issue (search open/merged PRs mentioning the issue ID). Omit the PR line entirely when no code PR exists.
3. Suggest one concrete recommended follow-up (next issue, merge step, or verification). Use "None — no immediate follow-up identified." only when nothing applies.
4. Send the message using SendSlackMessage.

## Message template

### In Review
:eyes: _{ISSUE_ID} — {ISSUE_TITLE}_ is In Review.

_Summary:_ {summary}

_Linear:_ {linear_url}

{optional_pr_line}

_Recommended follow-up:_ {follow_up}

### Done
:white_check_mark: _{ISSUE_ID} — {ISSUE_TITLE}_ is Done.

_Summary:_ {summary}

_Linear:_ {linear_url}

{optional_pr_line}

_Recommended follow-up:_ {follow_up}

## Rules
- Use the template that matches the new status (In Review or Done).
- `optional_pr_line` is `_PR:_ {pr_url}` when a PR exists; omit the line (and the blank line before follow-up) when it does not.
- Do not @mention the assignee unless the issue explicitly asks for it.
- Keep Slack mrkdwn: italics with underscores, links as <url|label> when a short label helps.
